anceps: qvi^s i^nho_spi^ta_li*s c[au]ca^si_ ru*p(e)m a_spe^ra*m

perseus: Heniochus habitans quisve Cecropiis metus
anceps: he*ni^o^chu^s ha^bi^ta*ns qvi_sve^ ce_cro^pi^i_s me^tu*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: terris Procrustes? genitor en natos premo
anceps: te*rri_s pro^cru_ste*s ge^ni^to^r e_n na*to_s pre^mo*

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: premorque natis— sceleris est aliquis modus.
anceps: pre*mo_rqve^ na_ti*s sce^le^ri^s e_st a^li^qvi_s mo^du*s

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: Sceleri modus debetur ubi facias scelus,
anceps: sce^le^ri_ mo^du_s de*be_tu^r u^bi^ fa^ci^a_s sce^lu*s

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: non ubi reponas. hoc quoque exiguum est mihi.
anceps: no*n u^bi^ re^po_na*s ho_c qvo^qv(e) e_xi^gu^(u)m e_st mi^hi*

speaker: ['#atreus']

anceps: e*x vu_lne^r(e) i_pso* sa_ngvi^ne_m ca^li^d(u)m i_n tu^a*

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: defundere ora debui, ut viventium
anceps: de*fu_nde^r(e) o_ra* de_bu^(i) u_t ui*ue_nti^u*m

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: biberes cruorem— verba sunt irae data
anceps: bi^be^re_s cru^o_re*m ve_rba^ su_nt i*r[ae] da^ta*

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: dum propero, ferro vulnera impresso dedi,
anceps: du*m pro^pe^ro^ fe_rro* uu_lne^r(a) i_mpre*sso_ de^di*

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: cecidi ad aras, caede votiva focos
anceps: ce*ci_d(i) a^d a_ra*s c[ae]de^ uo_ti*ua_ fo^co*s

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: placavi et artus, corpora exanima amputans,
anceps: pla*ca_v(i) e^t a_rtu*s co_rpo^r(a) e_xa^ni^m(a) a_mpu^ta*ns

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: in parva carpsi frusta et haec ferventibus
anceps: i*n pa_rva^ ca_rpsi* fru_st(a) e^t h[ae]c fe*rve_nti^bu*s

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: demersi aenis, illa lentis ignibus
anceps: de*me_rs(i) a^e_ni*s i_lla^ le_nti*s i_gni^bu*s

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: stillare iussi; membra nervosque abscidi
anceps: sti*lla_re^ ju_ssi* me_mbra^ ne_rvo*sqv(e) a_bsci^di*

perseus: viventibus, gracilique traiectas veru

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: mugire fibras vidi et aggessi manu
anceps: mu*gi_re^ fi_bra*s vi_d(i) e^t a_gge*ssi_ ma^nu*

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: fecisse potuit, cecidit in cassum dolor:
anceps: fe*ci_sse^ po^tu^i*t ce^ci^di^t i_n ca*ssu_m do^lo*r

speaker: ['#atreus']
perseus: scidit ore natos impio, sed nesciens,
anceps: sci^di^t o_re^ na_to*s i_mpi^o_ se*d ne_sci^e*ns

speaker: ['#atreus', '#thyestes']

anceps: se*d ne_sci^e_nte*s cl[au]sa^ li_to^ri^bu_s va^gi*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: audite maria, vos quoque audite hoc scelus,
anceps: [au]di_te^ ma^ri^a* vo_s qvo^qv(e) [au]di*t(e) ho_c sce^lu*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']

anceps: qvo*cu_mqve^ di_ fu*gi_sti^s [au]di*t(e) i_nfe^ri*

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: audite terrae, Noxque Tartarea gravis
anceps: [au]di_te^ te_rr[ae] no_xqve^ ta_rta^re^a_ gra^vi*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: et atra nube, vocibus nostris vaca
anceps: e*t a_tra^ nu_be* vo_ci^bu_s no*stri_s va^ca*

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: (tibi sum relictus, sola tu miserum vides,
anceps: ti^bi^ su_m re^li_ctu*s so_la^ tu_ mi^se^ru_m vi^de*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: tu quoque sine astris), vota non faciam improba,
anceps: tu* qvo^qve^ si^n(e) a_stri*s vo_ta^ no_n fa^ci^(a)m i_mpro^ba*

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: pro me nihil precabor— et quid iam potest
anceps: pro* me_ ni^hi_l pre*ca_bo^r e_t qvi*d ja_m po^te*st

perseus: tu, summe caeli rector, aetheriae potens
anceps: tu* su_mme^ c[ae]li* re_cto^r [ae]the^ri^[ae] po^te*ns

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: dominator aulae, nubibus totum horridis
anceps: do^mi^na_to^r [au]l[ae] nu_bi^bu_s to*t(u)m ho_rri^di*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: convolve mundum, bella ventorum undique
anceps: co*nvo_lve^ mu_ndu*m be_lla^ ve_nto*r(u)m u_ndi^qve*

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: committe et omni parte violentum intona,
anceps: co*mmi_tt(e) e^t o_mni* pa_rte^ vi^o^le*nt(u)m i_nto^na*

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: manuque non qua tecta et immeritas domos
anceps: ma*nu_qve^ no_n qva* te_ct(a) e^t i_mme^ri^ta_s do^mo*s

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: telo petis minore, sed qua montium
anceps: te*lo_ pe^ti_s mi*no_re^ se_d qva* mo_nti^u*m

speaker: ['#thyestes']

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: stabant pares Gigantes, hac arma expedi

perseus: iaculare flammas, lumen ereptum polo

perseus: fulminibus exple. causa, ne dubites diu,

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: utriusque mala sit; si minus, mala sit mea:

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: me pete, trisulco flammeam telo facem

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: humare et igni tradere extremo volo,

speaker: ['#thyestes']

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: nullumque telis impios numen petit,
anceps: nu*llu_mqve^ te_li*s i_mpi^o_s nu*me_n pe^ti*t

speaker: ['#thyestes']
perseus: aeterna nox permaneat et tenebris tegat

speaker: ['#thyestes']
